<br>
Resistance Is Futile X2<br>
<br>
Retask X5<br>
We Are the Borg<br>
<br>
A Change of Plans X8<br>
Adapt: Negate Obstruction X7<br>
Awaken X14<br>
<br>
Q Tent X10<br>
Transwarp Network Gateway X5 </span></TD></TR></TABLE></span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Strategy</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%" ><span class=text>Disregard the mistake of 2 Spacedoors..there is only one.<br>
<br>
Borg was the first affiliation I learned to play, so they have a special place in my heart--not to mention the STNG episode where Locutus was born!!<br>
I have gone through many stages with this deck and I now feel it is as close to my style of play as it is gonna get...till the Collective comes out.  I would appreciate any comments that may make this better; I will make some comments about changes I want to do, but I will like to hear your opinions.  This deck takes a little &quot;thinking&quot; when playing with, but enjoy...<br>
<br>
The Strategy:<br>
<br>
My perfect hand has 1 Q Tent, 1 A Change of Plans (ACOP), and 1 Awaken.  If you get more Awakens, the better, or a Queen or another Tent.  Your first turn you will d/l a scout vessel with the spacedoor, Awaken for Tactic drone (Hugh), move him and Complink drone onto scout vessel, Tent for the appropriate counterpart and end turn.  Second turn, discard a STP to return the scout vessel to hand, report it at end of spaceline (alpha or gamma, wherever their homeworld is) with counterpart, Hugh, Complink, and any other drones in hand, d/l TNG at end of spaceline.  Play ACOP to get Assimilate HW.  Move ship to HW and send a drone to scout.  You should have seeded Sheliak+Q+Matriarchal Society.  Your first drone will get stopped by Q.  Let him rearrange spaceline.  Big deal.  Send another drone to complete scouting--MS does not affect borg.  Flip Service the Collective and probe.  I do not know the exact probability of a successful probe, but 60 of the 106 cards are a good probe (around 57%).  If succesful...yeah!  If not...wait.  If the Sheliak does not kill your drones next turn, get them off.  Sheliak will not affect your objective.  If your opponent did not battle you, then you will probe your next turn.  Patiently wait on your scout vessel (if the right people are on it, it will be a 11-12-12 ship) and probe when you get the chance.  I have gotten a second turn HW assimilated about 7 out of 10 times.  Good enough odds for me.  Now, what if my opponent is not playing with the HWs?  I do not play with them so we do not have to double seed under duplicate missions.  Choose one of his planets (35 points or more) to Assimilate Planet.  Another problem is if he seeds under his HW.  You can take the chance.  If the dilemma stops you, it will delay the probing, but not forever.  In the games I have played, I assimilated the HW, and then solved my objectives on his missions.  I have rarely solved them on my own missions.  If he is playing in the gamma quadrant, go for his homeworld (this will practically shut him down) and solve whatever mission you want.  Adapt tricky dilemmas that stop you, remember, the Borg generally rip through anything (stopped by Founder Secret, Adapt it next turn, and lose only one drone to the flying pancakes :P).<br>
In the meantime, you will be setting up drones and the Queen at your outpost to prepare for the arrival of the cube; then go mission solving.  <br>
<br>
Note:  It is possible to Assimilate Homeworld in the first turn--if they are playing Romulan or Klingon with their respective homeworlds--your opening hand will need to consist of either Gowron or Tomalak, a scout vessel, one other drone (preferably 2), and ACOP...go get him!!<br>
<br>
<br>
Other notes:<br>
<br>
Extra counterparts=lucky draw against opponent or a good probe.<br>
Flexibility-I can do anything on the fly if needed, and battle...take out his one ship he fortunately got out before Assimilate HW.<br>
Resistance is Futile-game winner (Assimilate HW, 2 Establish Gateways+one Resistance)<br>
Retask-quick staffed cube..nuff said.<br>
14 Awakens!!!-free reports (d/l) and good probe.<br>
Dilemmas-take out their science.<br>
Mission selection-5 require science (anti-stealing when in conjunction with my dilemmas), and if they want to steal Samaritan Snare for 15 points...be my guest, then I will Establish Gateway (likely in one turn against the right affiliation).<br>
<br>
Problems:<br>
I am pretty much the only Borg player in my area, so I do not know how this will fair against another Borg...I guess go mission solving...shrug.<br>
STP drop is common here...I let them drop then Eliminate Starship (works well if I get HW).<br>
Q bypass...seed carefully and if you know he is bypassing, then use the Hide &amp; Seek as a Hidden Agenda. <br>
Armadas...use Multiplexor or if they are in the alpha quadrant, go solving in the gamma.<br>
Nors...if anyone has ideas, please let me know.  I do know if they seeded it at a planet I can assimilate, they are mine, but other than that...shrug.<br>
I want to add another Obelisk/Masaka combo...good idea, or not?  I would take out the Long Live the Queen, but is it worth it?<br>
Also, I would like to put a Revolving Door in the Tent...good idea?<br>
And any suggestions on the dilemmas....<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
<br>
DarthPapa<br>
<br>
PS: I almost beat last years state champion with a similar deck (it had minus 1 Assimilate Planet, 1 Establish Gateway, and the Resistance was not in the Tent); he won 100-95.  If those were in, I would have had him.  So, now the changes are made.  Hopefully you guys can help make it World ready.  :)   </span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><A HREF="deckread.php3?deck=87"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/read.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF="deckreview.php3?deck=87"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/review.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><a href="decks.php3"><img src="/stccg/global/images/back.gif" border="0" ></a></TD><TD><a href="deckprint.php3?deck=87" TARGET="BLANK_"><img src="/stccg/global/images/print.gif" border="0"></a></TD></TR></TABLE> </span></td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>
